{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 11:24:44.471070", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Network Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope and context\n- Hierarchical enterprise network using OSPF across cores/distribution, with hosts on 10.<core>.<dist>.0/24 subnets, DHCP via relays at distribution, DNS and web services in 10.200.0.0/24, and an Nginx load balancer fronting private backend web servers (not directly reachable by hosts).\n\nHigh-level health assessment\n- Routing/OSPF: Healthy. Distribution routers have OSPF-learned routes to server networks and across core links. Latency and ICMP reachability across the routed domain are normal.\n- Web and DNS services: Healthy. DNS name resolution is fast and consistent. HTTP to the load balancer (web99.local) succeeds with reasonable TTFB and totals. Direct access to public web servers (web0–web3) is reachable as expected.\n- Backend isolation: Enforced. Hosts cannot reach the backend web segment (20.200.0.0/24), consistent with design.\n- Access network host status: Mixed. Host in 10.1.1.0/24 has a working (dynamic) IP; host in 10.2.1.0/24 has no IP address.\n\nDetected anomalies\n1) DHCP failure on access subnet 10.2.1.0/24 (and impending risk for 10.1.1.0/24):\n- host_2_1_1_1 has link up (eth0 up, link detected 10G) but no IPv4 address or routes, indicating it did not obtain DHCP.\n- Both distribution routers show isc-dhcp-relay service inactive (dead).\n  - router_dist_1_1: isc-dhcp-relay inactive (dead)\n  - router_dist_2_1: isc-dhcp-relay inactive (dead)\n- The DHCP server (10.200.0.8) is up and reachable from router_dist_2_1 via OSPF; ICMP to the server succeeds (rtt ~1.4–2.5 ms). This isolates the failure to relay on the distribution layer rather than server reachability.\n- host_1_1_1_1 currently has an active, dynamically assigned address (10.1.1.10/24) with very short remaining lease time (valid_lft ~53s reported at inspection), indicating it likely obtained a lease earlier when relay was functioning; renewal would fail while the relay remains down.\n\n2) Reachability inventory observations\n- get_reachability shows host_2_1_1_1 has no IP and no test results to or from it (status unknown), consistent with DHCP failure on its VLAN.\n- All tested server-side nodes (dns_server, load_balancer, web_server_0–3) can reach each other with low latency.\n- host_1_1_1_1 can ICMP the server farm (10.200.0.2–.7) with normal latency and zero loss.\n- Attempting to reach backend_web_0 (20.200.0.2) from host_1_1_1_1 fails with “Destination Net Unreachable” from 10.1.1.1—expected by design (backend not advertised/accessible).\n\nLocalization\n- Fault lies at the distribution layer, specifically the DHCP relay function on router_dist_1_1 and router_dist_2_1. Physical layer is fine on host_2_1_1_1 (link up), routing core is healthy (OSPF routes present and functional), DHCP server is up and reachable from the distribution layer, and access switches are bridging as expected. The absence of DHCP relay is preventing broadcast DHCP from reaching the central server.\n\nRoot cause\n- DHCP relay services are not running on both distribution routers (isc-dhcp-relay inactive/dead on router_dist_1_1 and router_dist_2_1), thereby blocking DHCP request forwarding from access VLANs to the central DHCP server. This causes host_2_1_1_1 to have no IP address and presents an imminent renewal failure risk for hosts in 10.1.1.0/24 as current leases expire.\n\nEvidence highlights\n- host_2_1_1_1: No inet address; link up (ethtool speed 10000Mb/s, Link detected: yes). ip_route empty.\n- router_dist_1_1 and router_dist_2_1: isc-dhcp-relay inactive (dead).\n- dhcp_server: isc-dhcp-server active (running).\n- router_dist_2_1 -> 10.200.0.8 ping: success, low RTT.\n- host_1_1_1_1: DHCP dynamic address 10.1.1.10 with short valid_lft; default via 10.1.1.1.\n- host_1_1_1_1 -> dns_server/load_balancer/web_server_0–3 ICMP: success; curl http://web99.local: TTFB ~0.21–0.33s, total ~1.01–1.13s; DNS name lookup ~5ms.\n- host_1_1_1_1 -> backend_web_0 (20.200.0.2): Destination Net Unreachable from 10.1.1.1 (expected isolation).", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 11040, "output_tokens": 3874, "total_tokens": 14914, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 10880}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2752}}}
